              "a": "The cost of a small business law attorney varies based on case complexity, attorney experience, geographic location, and billing method. Hourly rates typically range from $200 to $500 per hour.  Some attorneys offer flat fee arrangements ranging from $1,000-$5,000 for straightforward matters. Retainer fees typically range from $3,000-$10,000. Major metropolitan areas command higher rates than rural areas. Attorney experience significantly impacts pricing, with seasoned specialists charging more than general practitioners. Always get a detailed written fee agreement before hiring an attorney, and ask about all potential costs including filing fees, expert witnesses, and other expenses that may arise during your case."
